{"TopicId":145937,"ForumId":46,"TopicTitle":"What\u0026#039;s the deal with \u0026quot;following?\u0026quot;","CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T16:11:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T16:11:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have explicitly followed a few threads I don\u0027t want to lose track of... when I check my followed threads... it\u0027s every single thread I have ever posted into, which makes \u0022following\u0022 100% useless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI see no setting for this at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T16:18:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(82,82,82);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EFollowing downtime on July 25th a lot of \u0027follow user\u0027 records were unfortunately lost.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(82,82,82);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EI don\u0027t know if\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ethe downtime affected just \u0027follow user\u0027 records or if it affected all followed content for some users, but this could be why\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-14T16:20:18Z\u0022 title=\u002208/14/2016 04:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Galileo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T21:41:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222716910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471191537\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(82,82,82);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EFollowing downtime on July 25th a lot of \u0027follow user\u0027 records were unfortunately lost.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(82,82,82);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EI don\u0027t know if\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ethe downtime affected just \u0027follow user\u0027 records or if it affected all followed content for some users, but this could be why\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems to be just \u0022follow user\u0022 stuff, my followed threads were unaffected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T21:57:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222716904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471191102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have explicitly followed a few threads I don\u0027t want to lose track of... when I check my followed threads... it\u0027s every single thread I have ever posted into, which makes \u0022following\u0022 100% useless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI see no setting for this at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, there is. At the very top of the screen there\u0027s a box that says \u0022follow\u0022 in a light grey arrow that points to a number. If you click that box, you can either follow or unfollow the forum tread. If you reply to any thread, the forum defaults to it as an indication you want to follow a thread. Simply revisit the thread, click the \u0022follow link\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA new box will pop up where you can set your notification preferences. Simply click the red \u0022UNFOLLOW\u0022 button on the lower right of the box.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-14T21:59:11Z\u0022 title=\u002208/14/2016 09:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by adsii1970\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Andem","CreatedById":155578,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T22:17:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222716904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471191102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have explicitly followed a few threads I don\u0027t want to lose track of... when I check my followed threads... it\u0027s every single thread I have ever posted into, which makes \u0022following\u0022 100% useless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI see no setting for this at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can change that in \u0022Notifications Settings\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T22:45:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I have used the follow at the top of the page. I checked my followed threads, and every thread I had posted in was marked followed. I turned the settings off, then on again, and that seemed to fix it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T18:52:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight now the little box in the top right is checked and\u00A0says I am following THIS thread, and guess what, I\u0027m not following this thread.\u00A0I never told it to follow this thread. Every thread I post in gets followed, then I have to unfollow it. This defeats the purpose. I thought I had fixed it, but if I have to do something with every thread, I might as well just ignore the functionality (since there isn\u0027t\u00A0any).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T19:18:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222720385\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471459974\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight now the little box in the top right is checked and\u00A0says I am following THIS thread, and guess what, I\u0027m not following this thread.\u00A0I never told it to follow this thread. Every thread I post in gets followed, then I have to unfollow it. This defeats the purpose. I thought I had fixed it, but if I have to do something with every thread, I might as well just ignore the functionality (since there isn\u0027t\u00A0any).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry clicking the notification bell icon at the top of the page and then \u0022Notification Settings\u0022, the options to auto-follow threads you start or reply to are there. Won\u0027t help with the stuff you\u0027ve already followed but will keep new ones from being added unless you do so explicitly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T19:21:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222720413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471461495\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry clicking the notification bell icon at the top of the page and then \u0022Notification Settings\u0022, the options to auto-follow threads you start or reply to are there. Won\u0027t help with the stuff you\u0027ve already followed but will keep new ones from being added unless you do so explicitly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOMG, thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked for it under, you know, \u0022Settings\u0022 under my name, where I expected all settings to reside. It never occurred to me to look under notifications.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T19:23:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222720418\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471461685\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOMG, thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked for it under, you know, \u0022Settings\u0022 under my name, where I expected all settings to reside. It never occurred to me to look under notifications.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155578-andem/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155578\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155578-andem/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Andem\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0you should be repping, check out the reply further up thread. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T19:25:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept I could not find \u0022notification settings\u0022 where they belong, under \u0022settings.\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Andem","CreatedById":155578,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T20:21:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222720424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471461825\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155578-andem/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155578\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155578-andem/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Andem\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0you should be repping, check out the reply further up thread. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re the one who gave details...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-18T00:51:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think \u0022following\u0022 is working anyway.\u00A0 Just recently (after July 25th) I \u0022followed\u0022 the Daily Kerbal forum and I don\u0027t get any notifications at all when a new thread is posted there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Andem","CreatedById":155578,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-18T02:12:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222720722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471481497\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think \u0022following\u0022 is working anyway.\u00A0 Just recently (after July 25th) I \u0022followed\u0022 the Daily Kerbal forum and I don\u0027t get any notifications at all when a new thread is posted there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY\u0027know, know that I think about it, that happens to me too. Could that be because the SQUAD account is anomalous?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-18T02:15:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222720722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471481497\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI \u0022followed\u0022 the Daily Kerbal forum and I don\u0027t get any notifications at all when a new thread is posted there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t had any luck with following whole subforums either, only individual threads (haven\u0027t tried following another user).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}